[{"id":"VR598323","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two diagrams, labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. In each figure there are two pucks, labeled A and B, such that Puck A is on the left and Puck B is on the right. Figure 1 is labeled “Before Collision,” and shows Puck A and Puck B moving toward each other at the same speed. Figure 2, labeled “After Collision,” shows Puck A and Puck B both moving to the right, with Puck B moving at a faster speed than Puck A.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR598323.g02.svg\"/></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two pucks, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span>, with unequal masses, slide with equal speeds in opposite directions on a horizontal surface with negligible friction, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The pucks undergo a head-on collision. After the collision, both pucks move to the right. The speed of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> has decreased, and the speed of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> has increased, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following is a plausible explanation for the observed behavior of the pucks?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR598323_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of change in momentum is the same for each puck, but Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> has more momentum initially.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of change in momentum is the same for each puck, but Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> has more momentum initially.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of change of momentum is the same for each puck because each puck has the same momentum initially.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of change in momentum of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> is greater than that of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> because Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> has a greater initial momentum.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The magnitude of change of momentum of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> is less than that of Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> because Puck <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> has greater mass.</p>"],"answer":0}]